<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="620" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="0.[1250,2131,610,761]" pageId="0" pageNumber="620">• Large insectivores with long flexible snouts, sometimes supported by unique bony os proboscis, and dental venom delivery system with deeply grooved second lower incisor associated with enlarged submaxillary gland.</paragraph>
